'''''Emilia Pérez''''' ({{IPA|es-419|eˈmilja ˈpeɾes|lang}}) is a 2024 French [[Musical film|musical]] [[Crime film|crime]] [[comedy film]] written and directed by [[Jacques Audiard]]. Based on Audiard's [[opera libretto]] of the same name, which was inspired by the 2018 novel ''Écoute'' by Boris Razon, the film follows a Mexican cartel leader ([[Karla Sofía Gascón]]) who enlists a lawyer ([[Zoe Saldaña]]) to help her disappear so that she may [[Gender transition|transition into a woman]]. [[Selena Gomez]], [[Adriana Paz]], [[Mark Ivanir]] and [[Édgar Ramírez]] also appear in starring roles.

[[Principal photography]] took place from May to July 2023 in the [[Île-de-France]]. The choreographic sections of the film were designed by [[Damien Jalet]]. The songs and score were composed by [[Camille (French singer)|Camille]] and [[Clément Ducol]], respectively.

''Emilia Pérez'' had its world premiere on 18 May 2024 at the [[2024 Cannes Film Festival|77th Cannes Film Festival]], where it won the [[Jury Prize (Cannes Film Festival)|Jury Prize]] and the [[Cannes Film Festival Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] award for its female ensemble. It was theatrically released by [[Pathé]] in France on 21 August 2024. The film

